---
// Whispr architecture diagram, pure inline SVG, no JS.
//
// Shows the journey of a single message: plaintext on Alice's device →
// X3DH + Double Ratchet session → AES-256-GCM ciphertext → wire → Bob's
// device decrypts. Three transport paths (LAN, Tor, BLE) sit in the
// middle channel, and the "no server in the picture" callout makes the
// architectural absence explicit.
//
// Design constraints:
//   - No JS, no client-side rendering. SVG inlined at build time.
//   - Text in monospace to match the editorial / terminal-panel style.
//   - Site palette only, accent #00d4aa, surface #131316, bg #0b0b0d,
//     border #23232a, secondary #a3a3a3, hint #737373.
//   - Wraps in <figure> with <figcaption> so screen readers get the
//     plain-text equivalent without us hiding the SVG.
//   - viewBox-based, so it scales down to mobile without media queries.
---

<figure class="my-8">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 800 500"
    class="w-full h-auto max-w-3xl mx-auto block"
    role="img"
    aria-labelledby="arch-diagram-title arch-diagram-desc"
  >
    <title id="arch-diagram-title">Whispr architecture diagram</title>
    <desc id="arch-diagram-desc">
      A message originates as plaintext on the sender's device, passes
      through an X3DH + Double Ratchet session, gets encrypted with
      AES-256-GCM, and travels as ciphertext over LAN, Tor, or BLE mesh
      directly to the recipient. There is no server, no account, and no
      telemetry between the two devices.
    </desc>

    <!-- ── ALICE'S DEVICE ──────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <rect x="40" y="40" width="220" height="340" rx="14"
            fill="#131316" stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="150" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">ALICE'S DEVICE</text>

      <!-- Plaintext -->
      <rect x="60" y="90" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="150" y="113" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#ffffff">Plaintext message</text>

      <!-- arrow down -->
      <path d="M 150 130 L 150 144 M 146 140 L 150 144 L 154 140"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- X3DH session -->
      <rect x="60" y="148" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="150" y="171" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">X3DH + Double Ratchet</text>

      <!-- arrow down -->
      <path d="M 150 188 L 150 202 M 146 198 L 150 202 L 154 198"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- AES-256-GCM -->
      <rect x="60" y="206" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="150" y="229" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">AES-256-GCM</text>

      <!-- E2EE boundary -->
      <text x="150" y="261" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">END-TO-END BOUNDARY</text>
      <line x1="60" y1="270" x2="240" y2="270"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            stroke-opacity="0.55"/>

      <!-- Encrypted blob -->
      <rect x="60" y="284" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="150" y="307" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#737373">Encrypted blob</text>

      <!-- arrow exiting device -->
      <path d="M 150 332 L 150 374 M 146 370 L 150 374 L 154 370"
            stroke="#737373" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
    </g>

    <!-- ── CENTER · TRANSPORT CHANNELS ─────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <text x="400" y="60" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">DIRECT P2P · NO RELAY</text>

      <!-- LAN -->
      <line x1="260" y1="200" x2="540" y2="200"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <rect x="345" y="190" width="110" height="20" rx="10"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
      <text x="400" y="204" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            fill="#00d4aa">LAN</text>

      <!-- Tor -->
      <line x1="260" y1="240" x2="540" y2="240"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <rect x="345" y="230" width="110" height="20" rx="10"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
      <text x="400" y="244" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            fill="#00d4aa">TOR · .onion</text>

      <!-- BLE -->
      <line x1="260" y1="280" x2="540" y2="280"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
      <rect x="345" y="270" width="110" height="20" rx="10"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.5"/>
      <text x="400" y="284" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="10"
            fill="#00d4aa">BLE MESH</text>

      <!-- Wire-bytes annotation -->
      <text x="400" y="335" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">ON THE WIRE</text>
      <text x="400" y="352" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#a3a3a3">Encrypted bytes only</text>
    </g>

    <!-- ── BOB'S DEVICE ─────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <rect x="540" y="40" width="220" height="340" rx="14"
            fill="#131316" stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="650" y="68" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">BOB'S DEVICE</text>

      <!-- arrow entering device from below (rendered first so it's behind boxes) -->
      <path d="M 650 374 L 650 332 M 646 336 L 650 332 L 654 336"
            stroke="#737373" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- Encrypted blob -->
      <rect x="560" y="284" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="650" y="307" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#737373">Encrypted blob</text>

      <!-- E2EE boundary -->
      <line x1="560" y1="270" x2="740" y2="270"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            stroke-opacity="0.55"/>
      <text x="650" y="261" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9"
            letter-spacing="1.5" fill="#737373">END-TO-END BOUNDARY</text>

      <!-- AES-256-GCM -->
      <rect x="560" y="206" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="650" y="229" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">AES-256-GCM</text>

      <!-- arrow up -->
      <path d="M 650 202 L 650 188 M 646 192 L 650 188 L 654 192"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- X3DH session -->
      <rect x="560" y="148" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
      <text x="650" y="171" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#00d4aa">X3DH + Double Ratchet</text>

      <!-- arrow up -->
      <path d="M 650 144 L 650 130 M 646 134 L 650 130 L 654 134"
            stroke="#00d4aa" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>

      <!-- Plaintext -->
      <rect x="560" y="90" width="180" height="36" rx="6"
            fill="#0b0b0d" stroke="#23232a"/>
      <text x="650" y="113" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#ffffff">Plaintext message</text>
    </g>

    <!-- ── BOTTOM BAND · NOT IN THE PICTURE ────────────────────────── -->
    <g>
      <line x1="40" y1="410" x2="760" y2="410"
            stroke="#23232a" stroke-width="1"/>
      <text x="400" y="438" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            letter-spacing="2" fill="#737373">NOT IN THE PICTURE</text>
      <text x="400" y="468" text-anchor="middle"
            font-family="ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11"
            fill="#a3a3a3">No server · No account · No phone number · No telemetry · No cloud</text>
    </g>
  </svg>

  <figcaption class="text-hint text-xs font-mono text-center mt-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
    A message originates as plaintext on the sender's device, passes through an X3DH + Double Ratchet session, is encrypted with AES-256-GCM, and travels as ciphertext over LAN, Tor, or BLE mesh, directly to the recipient. There is no server, account, or telemetry between the two devices.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
